# Placeholder for the RECOVERY OTA bundle signing pubkey (D54).
#
# Distinct from the primary key. The recovery key's seckey lives only on
# paper in a safe + encrypted in a separate physical location — it never
# touches CI. If the primary signing key is ever leaked, the recovery key
# signs a rotation image that ships a new primary pubkey.
#
# At build time, CI replaces this file's contents with the actual recovery
# pubkey. The real pubkey lands in the baked image as
# /etc/agora/update-pubkey-recovery.pem. This .example file is committed
# only so that local builds have something present.

-----BEGIN MINISIGN PUBLIC KEY (RECOVERY) — PLACEHOLDER -----
TODO-substituted-at-build-time-by-CI
-----END MINISIGN PUBLIC KEY -----
